default&#xa0;defaultClinical Accessdefault4.1default 
defaultAs well as delivering financial benefits, investing in Clinical Access also supports patient engagement and involvement at the point of care, improvements in care and 
defaultalso in delivering 
defaultNHS initiatives such as the drive to become paperless by
default 2018.
default&#xa0;
default4.2default 
defaultThe service provides staff with decision-making information and data capture in real time
default. It also serves as 
defaulta platform from which 
defaultstaff
default can access a range of applications directly at the bedside, including Picture Arching and Communications Sy
defaultstems (PACS), blood results and ordering, e-pharmacy, patient admissions systems, and even patient records, thereby reducing the reliance on paper based processes.
default&#xa0;
default4.3default 
defaultInterviews with NHS Managers confirm that using the service releases the equivalent of 
default14 members of staff per year, releasing time to be spent on delivering patient care and producing a time saving valued at £335k per annum, while the production saving generated through avoiding the volume of paper currently produced for each in-patient
default saves £60k.
default 
defaultThe sites at which 
defaultClinical Access
default is already in use include Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust, Guy’s and St Thomas’ NHS Foundation Trust and Cambridge University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust.
default&#xa0;defaultReal Time Patient Feedbackdefault (RTPF)default5.1default 
defaultOne of the key themes identified by the Francis Report was the importance of 
defaultlistening to patients, in real time, and using that feedback to improve outcomes
default.
default 
default&#xa0;
default5.2default 
defaultRTPF collects and aggregates patient feedback in real time, providing the opportunity to review the data from hospital-wide results to granular, ward-level feedback, s
defaultupporting immediacy in responding to the information captured.
default&#xa0;
default5.3default 
defaultAnalysis by Picker Institute Europe reveals that the service provides higher response rates providing a more representative view, unbiased data and a respondent profile that includes tradi
defaulttionally hard-to-reach demographics such as young and 
defaultethnically diverse
default patients
default.
